                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The first of two volumes of an incomplete <title
                                xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2149">Shāhnāmah</title> (Book of
                            Kings), by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Abū al-Qāsim Manṣūr
                                Firdawsī (fl. ca. 940–1020)</persName>, together with <ref
                                target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26519"
                                    ><idno>Persian MS 1000</idno></ref>. It opens with a shortened
                            redaction of the Baysunghur preface, followed by the poem proper, of
                            which Abū Manṣūr Daqīqī (d. ca. 980) commenced a thousand lines, but
                            after his death, Firdawsī completed the work shortly before the year
                                <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1000">1000 CE</date>. He drew upon
                            a number of pre-Islamic Pahlavi middle Persian sources, principally the
                            now-lost <title>Khwadāynāmag</title> (Book of Lords) that recounted the
                            ancient rulers of Persian until the Sassanian period, as well as Iranian
                            mythology and folklore.</summary>
